===Glyph origin===
{{Han etyl}}
{{liushu|p}}: a [[bird]] [[fly]]ing [[upwards]].

In its modern form, resembles a tasseled {{zh-l|升}}.

===Etymology===
From {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*mV-pjər|t=to [[fly#Verb|fly]]}}. Cognate to {{cog|bo|འཕུར|tr='phur}} and {{cog|grt|bila}}. 

This term also greatly resembles to {{cog|mkh-pro|*par||to fly}}, from whence comes {{cog|omx|ပဝ်|tr=pɔ}} and {{cog|mkh-vie-pro|*pər||to fly}} (whereas {{cog|vi|bay}}).

Related to {{cog|och|翂||tr=*pɯn|appearance of [[bird]]s flying [[slowly]]}} and {{cog|och|奮||tr=*pɯns|[[spread]] [[wing]]s and fly}}.

